rComments: Professor Tanner is a nice guy. The class included 2 exams, midterm and final. You have to write 2 essays and 50+ MCQ in 2 hours. TA (Storm) is very nice and her feedback for the term paper was very helpful. Professor Tanner is definitely a tough grader, he marked the final exam and the courses average below 70%.

He's definitely passionate about the material that he teaches. Personally I found the lectures a bit boring, and the readings a bit much. The course content was interesting at times though. Decent course, nothing fancy.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Fair professor, tough grader.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: This prof is the worst. I don't know why the university still has him there. its the 21st century not the 1800s stop using overheads. If the university wants to give a innovative learning experience, need to get rid of this prof. Can hardly understand him and cant even email him the essay or answer emails, you have to call him. Its a joke!

rComments: Tanner seems like a nice guy,but his lectures are EXTREMELY boring and not very helpful.This is not a easy course. Although the readings are super easy, exams are relatively tricky. The assignment also was marked harshly.
Bad. Do not take.

Hard to stay awake in this class. The readings are reasonable. However the exam often contains questions that's not from the book or lecture notes. He will briefly mention something and test you on it.

The workload is not very heavy for this course. Exams for the most part were fair with the exception of a few questions. The term paper/essay in my opinion was marked harshly/unfairly. The course may seem easy but it's not, be careful.

Tanner is a great professor! He's so helpful and the TA (Nathan) is so great! They only want to see you succeed in your academics! Yes, he's a little boring in the lectures but he's a really good man! Participate in class because a lot of the questions that he talks about in class are essay questions in the final !
Disappointed!

The course itself is pretty easy, not complex. A LOT of readings. He doesn't give specific reading time line, so you get behind. Lectures are really boring, half the class is asleep. Speaks in monotone british voice. DO NOT TAKE CLASS, but it is an easy class. Hard marker on essay. Very boring material.

He is not a bad prof at all. He tries to be funny. He takes a different approach than most profs do, but still tries to make classes interesting and engaging. This was a very interesting course. The exams were fair. You definitely need to attend class (essay questions) and read the text (M/C). The paper was also marked fairly.

Pretty uninspiring proffesor.  His lectures really drag on and he keeps making the same points over and over again.  I took sociology of education with him.  He went on for two classes talking about streaming in high schools and kept asking students what they think.  I kept thinking to myself, why did i wake up for this?

He's kinda boring sometimes and teaches in a very old school way, but he seems like a nice and sincere guy and he's not that bad of a prof. His exams are fair. He's not very organized though. But there are quite a bit of readings... especially because he doesn't specifically say what reading you need to do each week, it's very easy to fall behind.

He seems like a nice and easy going guy. His exams are pretty easy too but study the material well. If you studied then there are no tricks. He is kind of hard to understand sometimes. Oh, and he's very old-fashioned in his teaching style in that he uses projectors (those used in highschool)- not ppt slides, but he manually puts on each slide
Tanner, is the best prof.  he's very clear and approachable. do the readings and you'll do fine. mid term and final have no surprises!!! loved taking his classes.

Seems like a nice guy. Sometimes hard to understand cuz of his British accent. Very easy mid-term exam. All MC and no tricky ones. If you did the readings and goto lecture you'll be fine. Good Class overall
took sociology of education with him. his exam is ridiculously easy, no tricks. essay is hard to wrap your head around. definitely possible to get an A in this course.

He isn't helpful at all.  The guy has a strict policy on late papers.  But when I spoke to him about his multiple choice questions, he did give the class a sample.  He isn't that hard and neither is the course.  But no extension on the essays.

even thoguh he's boring and bland teaching style..i dinf him to be very reasonable...i always do well in his classes and i look forward ot taking any class of his. i took 3 classes withj him before and his exams are very predictable as long as u read the material and he's a fair marker
Boring prof. who mumbles so much that its hard to hear him. Very unapproachable and doesn't even listen to you. Don't take any of his classes. Just a very weird and awkward prof.
interesting class, it shows some aspects of the issue realted to the sociology of work. covered topics are related to real life and tells us how it really is out there:))Prof. is great too
Good professor
A great prof

I've had him for Work and Industry and Sociology of Education. If you want an easy class that is straight-forward: take one of his classes! It's like a high school class (he was a HS teacher once!) Plus hes got good stories (David Bowie played at his school before he was famous). Classes were great!
No Comments

A very effective and lighthearted professor.  Lecture has concrete examples, reading is well chosen to reflect course, useful stories, and tests are fair, if not abit hard.  Enjoyable class that uses current material and events as examples

This professor is AWESOME. He is clear, there are no suprises on the exam. Coming to his lectures are very enjoyable. I recommend the sociology of crime and deviance especially.  He is very straight forward and the text book is very helpful.
Mid term is easy, but he will kill you on the final
